The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | WI restrict Sri Lanka 
                                                                                                                                                                                                     WI restrict Sri Lanka 
                      
	Port of Spain: Chamara Kapugedera (95) and Chamara Silva (67) put on a sixth wicket partnership of 159 to turn around Sri Lankas innings in their one-day game against the West Indies on Thursday and set the hosts a target of 236.         
	Sri Lanka had been reeling at 49 for five after Dwayne Bravo claimed three early wickets for the West Indies before the pair resurrected their teams chances at the Queens Park Oval. Bravo ended with figures of four for 33.           (REUTERS)                                                                                                                      
